<TITLE> Take govt services to people: PM </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Mar 4 (bdnews24.com)--Prime minister Sheikh Hasina has asked for taking government services to the people instead of waiting for them to come. She launched Digital Innovation Fair 2010 at Bangabandhu Novo Theatre on Thursday and said her government was elected to office on the polls pledge of advancement of information technology. Hasina hoped that ICT would help to ensure transparency and accountability of the government, establish rule of law and purge the country of corruption. The prime minister stressed greater use of ICT in the public and public sectors. She also asked related authorities to arrange such fair in districts and upazilas to make people aware of ICT and other digital services. Access to Information Programme, Prime Minister's Office and the ministry of Science and ICT have co-organised the three-day fair. State minister for ICT Yafes Osman and UNDP resident coordinator Renata Lok Dessalien were special guests. b
